    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-10-14T19:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-10-14T19:26:00-05:00" n="300"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <head>300. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission to the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d300fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 299, Agency Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, Vol. V. Secret; Exdis.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-10-15T00:26:00+00:00">October 15, 1970,
                        0026Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2464. Subj: <gloss target="#t_CHIR1">Chirep</gloss>. Refs: <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> 2302; SecState 167550.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d300fn2">See <ref target="#d298">Document 298</ref> and <ref
                            target="#d298fn3">footnote 3 thereto</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>MisOffs (<persName corresp="#p_NMH1">Newlin</persName> and Romine) went
                        over ground in <gloss target="#t_REFTEL1">reftel</gloss>s with <persName
                            corresp="#p_HYC1">Hsueh</persName> (<gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>)
                        October 14. US and <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> anticipated shifts
                        coincided in cases of Bolivia, Cambodia, Canada, Chile and Malaysia. This
                        resulted in <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> estimated vote on Albanian
                            <gloss target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> of 49–53–24.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>MisOffs then informed <persName corresp="#p_HYC1">Hsueh</persName> of
                        possible trouble in cases of: Colombia, Peru, Italy, Luxembourg, Kuwait,
                        Cameroon, <gloss target="#t_CAR1">CAR</gloss>, Sierra Leone and
                        Tunisia.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HYC1">Hsueh</persName> took our most pessimistic
                        estimate (<gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> 2302) with sangfroid
                        observing that it unlikely that worst would eventuate in all cases. We
                        agreed and said our present forecast was for adoption of <gloss
                            target="#t_IQ1">IQ</gloss>
                        <gloss target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> and defeat of Albanian <gloss
                            target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> with much narrower margin than last
                        year.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>We agreed to following division of labor: <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>
                                <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> to make further efforts both
                                here and in capitals with: Bolivia, where <gloss target="#t_GRC1"
                                    >GRC</gloss> has active Spanish speaking Ambassador; Cameroon;
                                    <gloss target="#t_CAR1">CAR</gloss> (<persName corresp="#p_HYC1"
                                    >Hsueh</persName> says <persName corresp="#p_BJB1"
                                    >Bokassa</persName> is still in Taipei and that <gloss
                                    target="#t_CAR1">CAR</gloss> vote is safe); Mauritius; Guyana;
                                Peru; Sierra Leone.</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>US similarly to approach: Colombia, Iceland, Fiji, Luxembourg,
                                Morocco and Tunisia.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HYC1">Hsueh</persName> said Indonesian PermRep
                            <persName corresp="#p_AHR1">Abdulgani</persName> has told him again that
                        Indonesia will be absent from room at time vote taken.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HYC1">Hsueh</persName> agreed that if other side
                        dropped expulsion para from Albanian <gloss target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> or
                        brought about separate vote on operative paras (in expectation admission
                        para would achieve two-thirds majority while expulsion para would receive
                        only simple majority and would be eliminated) would face us with difficult
                        situation. <persName corresp="#p_HYC1">Hsueh</persName> agreed that in event
                        Albanian <gloss target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> were to receive simple majority
                        there would be serious difficulty when it came to plenary adoption of report
                        of Credentials Committee. He also agreed <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss>
                        would be placed in very precarious position in <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                            >SC</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>7.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> mission, he said, had been concentrating
                        on lobbying but he promised to reflect on above contingencies and to consult
                        further on best tactics.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_YCW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Yost</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
